programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding the Inner Girly Girl
programme.desc: Melissa Harris has devoted her life to raising her two young girls, but she's afraid she's falling short in her motherly duties. We're going to bring out the femme fatale in Melissa so she can be a super mom and role model.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back To Glamour
programme.desc: Rebecca gets a sophisticated makeover to bring back some of the glamour from her pre-mom days. Now, her husband can recognize the girl he married, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Fashion 911
programme.desc: Between two failed marriages, the loss of her father and caring for her ailing mother, Zoe feels life taking its toll on her appearance. She has found happiness in a new marriage, and she wants to feel confident when they are in public together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Frizzy to Fine
programme.desc: Zina is a makeup artist by trade – a woman who encourages people to look their best to show off their spirit. However, spending all her time working and taking care of her children, Zina realizes she doesn't live by her own advice.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Emma Singh
programme.desc: Busy mum and part time student Emma Singh has a taste for the bad things in life and it shows big time on her face. Cosmetic surgeon Jan Stanek plans to get Emma to travel more lightly and youthfully by ridding Emma of her excess baggage on day one.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Mr. Right

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Programming A New Look
programme.desc: Once upon a time, Ian was a groovy party DJ with long hair, spinning disco tunes. Now he's the computer dude with long gray hair. Intense skin treatments, lasik surgery and a Glam overhaul trim 10 years from his looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Hard Hat to Hottie

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: I'm No Grandma

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Self Conscious To Self Confident

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Firehouse

programme.title: Paranormal State: Paranormal Intervention
programme.desc: Carol Ann stays awake every night taping the voices of the dead. PRS cuts their winter break short to help her curtail her obsession and close this doorway to the dead--for good.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Room 37
programme.desc: Darrell and Cherry, the owners of an historic Tennessee bed and breakfast built in the late 1800s, are reporting apparitions of a man and hearing whistling throughout the hotel corridors.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Glove
programme.desc: When a terrifying haunting threatens to break a Daisytown, PA couple apart, PRS is their last resort. As the investigation deepens, PRS and the family learn that it's just the tip of iceberg, turns out this haunting might be all in the family.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Name
programme.desc: Ryan Buell and company set out on one of their most dangerous cases to date - to help a single mother who is experiencing paranormal activity in a home that was once the site of brutal murder.

programme.title: Paranormal State: They Only Come Out at Night
programme.desc: Once night falls in a quaint?New England Town, a police officer's family is terrorized by demons.?PRS arrives just in time with the family ready to vacate their family home, rather than suffer the advances of these spirit creatures.

programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Manifesto

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: John 3:16

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Red Highway
programme.desc: The elderly owners of a local grocery are attacked and left for dead. Working with a vague witness description, Lt. Joe Kenda leads a state-wide manhunt to catch a pair of cold-blooded killers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bad Dogs of Comedy

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Maxwell, Brooklyn, and Tipper

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sugar, Dax, Nixa, Pete, and Snowflake
programme.desc: Feuding German Shepherds vie to be top dog; Beagle has proven to be anything but sweet; Judi's Bichon Frise has forced her out of her own bed for fear of being bitten in the middle of the night.
programme.sub-title: Sugar, Dax, Nixa, Pete, and Snowflake

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Pack Leaders in Training
programme.desc: Cesar has always believed that kids are more receptive to his training methods than most adults. He flies two lucky young fans to California so they can become "Dog Whisperers" in training!

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cobar and Chase
programme.desc: Cesar takes a trip to Australia to help Cobar, a Koolie with a fear of squeaky toys. Then, he steps through the looking glass to help a Shar-pei mix who lunges at his own reflection in mirrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Mad Dogs: Mafia, Jack & Raspberry, Grady, Boo & Khia
programme.desc: Cesar arrives at an ad agency to help three dogs get along with the other dogs and their human co-workers. A couple needs help getting their border collie mix to relax in the car.
programme.sub-title: Mad Dogs: Mafia, Jack & Raspberry, Grady, Boo & Khia

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sadie and Calder
programme.desc: Allen and Erin Carrasco ‘s Basset Hound Sadie whines and moans whenever Allen is around. Blue Heeler mix Calder is a great dog by day, but bedtime rituals unleash unwelcome night terrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bull-Whipped
programme.desc: Aggressive bulldog Hugo is sent to canine rehab, and fellow bulldog Crusty must overcome his dominance issues if he's ever going to enjoy walks.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Married to a Doll/Picking My Scabs
programme.desc: Davecat has been married to his synthetic wife for 10 years. Meanwhile, Rachael hopes that her compulsive scab picking will stop by her wedding day.
programme.sub-title: Married to a Doll/Picking My Scabs

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Couch Cushion/Furry
programme.desc: While battling her addiction to eating couch cushions, Adele has destroyed 7 couches and 2 chairs. Meanwhile, Lauren is more comfortable in her fur suit than in her own skin.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to My Breasts/Tape Eater
programme.desc: Sheyla has spent $250,000 on 22 breast enlargement surgeries to achieve her 38KKK bust size, despite suffering a severe infection from her recent implants. Andrea is addicted to eating adhesive tape.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Greg Dreams of Jeannie_The Amazing Squirrel
programme.desc: Greg’s obsession with 60’s pop-culture has literally taken over his home. Kelly’s life revolves around her pet squirrel, Sugar Bush and his photo appearances.
programme.sub-title: Greg Dreams of Jeannie_The Amazing Squirrel

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Mannequin Invasion_Carrot Queen
programme.desc: Chad Michael is a mannequin fanatic. His collection of over 300 mannequins has taken over every room of his house. Zizi has 35 carrot tattoos and she’s decorated every room with a carrot theme.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Buggin' Out_Dumpster Diet
programme.desc: Bugs have been a part of David’s daily diet for over twelve years, watch as he braces himself to eat his most venomous bug yet. Kelly’s daily diet consists of food solely gathered from the dumpster.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Spin Cycle_Newborn Dolls
programme.desc: Fred and Robert have a rare collection of vintage washing machines. They’ve over $40,000 to compile this one-of-a-kind collection. Lynn has created over 1,800 life-like vinyl newborn dolls.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger
programme.desc: Bertha has been drinking up to five bottles of nail polish every day for the past five years but her family is worried she's doing permanent damage to her health. Jamie can't stop digging in her ears.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Grown-Up Baby
programme.desc: Stanley, 31, has been obsessed with being an adult baby for the past 18 years. Every day he wears footie pajamas, eats baby food, wears a diaper and sleeps in a crib.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: East Glass/Bleaches Skin
programme.desc: Josh has eaten more than 250 light bulbs. But is he really addicted to the attention that he receives? Candice thinks dark skin is ugly and has resorted to using dangerous bleaching creams.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Make-up Addict/Obsessed with Death
programme.desc: Maureen won't go out of the house without a full face of makeup. Meanwhile, Barbara is so obsessed with death that she's planned her own funeral.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Can’t Stop Cleaning/Love Rocks
programme.desc: Cyntrelle dropped out of high school because of her addiction to cleaning. Belinda's obsession with rocks has taken over her life, with more than 100,000 scattered around her home.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 1
programme.desc: “My Strange Addiction” tells the story of people who just can't stop doing very strange things, including a compulsive tanner, a runner, a shopper and a chalk eater.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Star Chaser_The Little Merman
programme.desc: Eric is obsessed with Mermaids and has transformed himself into a real-life Merman. Vanessa is so obsessed with meeting celebrities that she spends all day searching them out.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Striking It Rich
programme.desc: Carter and his wife Colleen have made millions from the bayou oil industry, so now they want a million dollar home on the water. In the bayou, that kind of money can buy luxury.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Tiki Hut Millionaires
programme.desc: Tiki King, Leo, and his fiancée, Stephanie, are looking for a waterfront castle on Perdido Bay. They are looking along the shores of Florida and Alabama to find the million-dollar home of their dreams.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Dock Party
programme.desc: Growing up on the bayous of Mississippi, Tommy and Mari are all about dock parties. Now they want a place of their own with an outdoor kitchen, and a huge dock.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Tropics
programme.desc: In Pensacola, Florida, life’s all about being out on your boat. After years of moving around the country with the US Air Force, there’s nowhere else Ron and his wife, Patty, want to live.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: $100,000 Waterfront Bargains
programme.desc: Captain Henry and his wife Danielle are looking for a waterfront home for less than $100,000. To find a bargain on the water they will travel between two states, Louisiana and Mississippi.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Crabman And His Clan
programme.desc: Houma, Louisiana is a hot spot for crabbing. That’s why commercial crabber Jordan and his wife Kayla want to move there. They’re looking for a waterfront home with a convenient commute for him.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Chic Mansions
programme.desc: Tyra Shepard loved going hunting with her husband, Kent, and created her own line of clothes for women of the bayou. Now they’re looking for their own million-dollar home in the bayou.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Swamps, Moss and Fast Boats
programme.desc: Drag boat racing couple Ryan and Linda are looking for a home on Caddo Lake. Ryan’s main focus is making sure he has a place to race and store his boats, but Linda is concerned about space.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Swamp and the City
programme.desc: Jazz musician, Jesse, and his Alaskan wife, Emilie, are looking for a waterfront home in New Orleans where they can stay close to Bourbon Street and within their tight budget.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Swampy Swimming Holes
programme.desc: Jeff and Gabby are looking for a house on a calm bayou with little boat traffic in Gulfport, Mississippi. But these waters are also rife with bayou wildlife – including gators.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cajun Pickle King
programme.desc: In the bayou, everything is pickled – from eggs to pigs’ feet. Matt’s family has been in the pickling business for more than 80 years. Business is booming so Matt wants the bayou home of his dreams.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bourbon St. to Bayous
programme.desc: The city of New Orleans is made up of 72 different neighborhoods, each with their own distinct bayou charm. Gene and his fiancée Elizabeth are looking for a Big Easy home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Ski Town
programme.desc: Woodville, Mississippi is a bayou ski town – waterskiing that is. Bayou newlyweds Dustin and Stephanie are looking find their own piece of waterfront heaven where they can boat, and ski!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Floating for a Bargain
programme.desc: Mac and his wife, Kelsey, are looking for a home for them and their 5-month-old daughter on the tubing paradise, the Bogue Chitto River.

programme.title: Baywatch: Baywatch at Sea World
programme.desc: Caroline finds herself being sued for negligence in civil court by the angry and bitter mother of a drowning victim. CJ babysits a neighbor’s newborn and realizes she wants to be a mother. But is Cody ready to be a father?

programme.title: Baywatch: Trial by Fire
programme.desc: CJ and Cody transport an injured sea lion to the animal recovery facility at Sea World. While there, Samantha gets the idea to promote lifeguarding by planning a Baywatch-theme stunt show at Sea World.

programme.title: Baywatch: Golden Girls
programme.desc: A crazed young woman is causing trouble on the Venice Boardwalk and Neely suspects it is more than meets the eye. Meanwhile, Newman meets his dream woman – who doesn’t speak English.

programme.title: Baywatch: Nevermore
programme.desc: A mysterious, disfigured man whom the public dubs "the phantom lifeguard," is secretly saving people and sending love notes to CJ. When CJ goes missing the team sets out to find her and the “phantom.”

programme.title: Baywatch: Rookie Summer
programme.desc: Young, ambitious and sexy lifeguard candidates compete for a chance to attend Rookie School. Mitch is offered a promotion to Captain and has a tough decision to make. Lani McKensie faces the sinister return of a former lover.

programme.title: Baywatch: Next Generation
programme.desc: Hobie, Lani, April and Skylar are among the trainees competing for a few open slots as Baywatch Lifeguards. Hobie isn't sure he wants to follow in his father's footsteps, but when a vengeful jet skier comes after April, Hobie comes to her rescue.

programme.title: Baywatch: The Choice
programme.desc: Veteran lifeguard Jack 'JD' Darius has a dark secret in his past. He comes to Baywatch to throw his rescue can in the ring for the open Lieutenant slot, but young and ambitious Taylor Walsh also wants the job, and she's ready to fight for it.

programme.title: Baywatch: Memorial Day
programme.desc: Mitch, Sky, and April find a dead man on the ocean floor. Their search for answers to his demise leads to the retirement home where he lived, and his two friends who seem to be hiding the true story. The chemistry between Cody and Lani heats up.

programme.title: Attack of the Killer Tomatoes
programme.desc: A group of scientists band together to save the world from mutated tomatoes that KILL! (1978)

programme.title: Creature from the Haunted Sea
programme.desc: In this spoof of horror and spy thrillers, American gangster Renzo Capetto decides to kill members of his bungling crew and blame their deaths on a legendary sea creature. What he doesn't know is that the creature is actually out there!

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre The Werewolf of Washington
programme.desc: While on assignment in Hungary, a young reporter is attacked by a mysterious animal. (1981)

programme.title: Lost Creek
programme.desc: After moving to a new town, 11-year-old Peter and his friend Bill must team up with mysterious new girl Maggie and brave the woods on Halloween to face a monster born from their nightmares.

programme.title: The Pack
programme.desc: A farmer and his family must fight for survival after a ferocious pack of wild dogs infiltrates their isolated farmhouse. Through a series of frightening and bloody encounters they are forced into survival mode to make it through the night.
